“Here's what I think integrity is: It's choosing courage over comfort. Choosing what's right over what's fun, fast or easy. And practicing your values.” - Brene Brown

We think this is an incredible acting tip!

When AFK&T kids choose to be actors, they discover they have to make hard choices like behaving professionally and graciously when their friend gets the part they wanted. Or, having to pass up the mall when they have an audition or need to study for showcase. Or, committing to their vision and dreams of being an actor when they haven't booked an audition or part in months and they're wondering what the heck they're doing. 
It's hard sometimes but it is about developing integrity and courage and these kids work on this every day that they go into class or show up for an audition or practice for showcase. These are the life lessons that get refined simply because they're willing to show up! http://ow.ly/Dc8530bM9mJ .
.

Happy Mother's Day! Spent this morning with my mama and then got a solid back day lift after a much needed rest day! Hope all you mom's out there are enjoying your day! I am so blessed to have a mother who has supported me and really raised me to become the woman I am today! Some of the most valuable things she has taught me in life are:
.
1. Keep it simple- the more complicated you make a situation, the more stress you are bringing on yourself, go with the flow and take things day by day.
2. Love yourself and others, do not judge people, do what makes you happy and support others who do so as well!
3. Who you are as a person is what matters, so don't care what others think, in the end good people will always shine through the bad! 💕
.
Mom's are true warriors, keep doin ya thang because we appreciate you more than you know!😘 #happymothersday
